RESULT 2: ZERO-MAGNETIZATION CONDITION
------------------------------------------------------------------------

  sum(cos(phi_k)) = 0 for ALL sectors (to machine precision):
    Charged Leptons (e, mu, tau) sum_cos = 0.00e+00
    Up-type Quarks (u, c, t)     sum_cos = -1.11e-16
    Down-type Quarks (d, s, b)   sum_cos = 0.00e+00

  This is a TAUTOLOGY of the 3-parameter Koide parametrization.
  The identity cos(x) + cos(x+2pi/3) + cos(x+4pi/3) = 0 holds
  for all x. Three parameters (M, a, theta0) fit three masses
  exactly, with 120-degree spacing built in by construction.
  The equal spacing is a coordinate choice, not a discovery.

